      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOMORROW WENDY (3) is a talented type who jumped from a squeeze box but quickly into stride and led throughout to score (17.91) at Richmond in Grade 5 over 320m. Superior out of the boxes and will be in the firing line early. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. HAYDEN'S FANCY (2) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only 0.8 lengths from Nicko Queen in second (20.86) at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from six attempts. Hard to beat again. NATURAL SPARK (8) found best form to score by a nose at this track over 365m (20.99) in a Grade 5. The form out of last race has been strong. Will go close again if runs up to latest. SUNSHINE SANDY (1) boasts a solid strike-rate from this box.",
